Residents of Nyalenda, Kisumu County on Tuesday held
demonstrations to protest the nullification of the Orange Democratic Movement’s
nomination results for Nyalenda A ward in Kisumu Central constituency. ODM’s appeals board overturned the Wednesday
nomination of the ward’s MCA aspirant Ratib Ahmed Boitone, citing
irregularities in the process. As per the Wednesday results, Ratib garnered 503
votes flooring his main rival and incumbent MCA Ojwang Ogendo who received 206
votes. The irate residents who lit bonfires and barricaded
feeder roads in the area accused ODM of high handedness, threatening to
withdraw their support in favour of parties affiliated with the Kenya Kwanza team  